'''Luiz Henrique André Rosa da Silva''' (born 2 January 2001), commonly known as '''Luiz Henrique''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|luˈiz͜ ẽj̃ˈʁi.ki}}), is a Brazilian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]] for [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Club career==
===Fluminense===
Born in [[Petrópolis]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], Luiz Henrique joined [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]]'s youth setup at the age of 9 in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/fluminense/noticia/cria-de-xerem-luiz-henrique-encanta-odair-no-fluminense-e-fura-fila-em-inicio-no-profissional.ghtml|title=Cria de Xerém, Luiz Henrique encanta Odair no Fluminense e "fura fila" em início no profissional|trans-title=Xérem-made, Luiz Henrique charms Odair at Fluminense and "jumps the line" in his professional beginnings|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|GloboEsporte.com]]|language=pt-BR|date=18 August 2020|accessdate=5 October 2020}}</ref> He made his first team – and [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] – debut on 12 August 2020, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Nenê (footballer, born 1981)|Nenê]] in a 1–1 home draw against [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/rj/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/12-08-2020/fluminense-palmeiras.ghtml|title=Artilheiros marcam, mas Fluminense e Palmeiras ficam no empate no Maracanã|trans-title=Goalscorers score, but Fluminense and Palmeiras end up drawing at the Maracanã|publisher=GloboEsporte.com|language=pt-BR|date=12 August 2020|accessdate=5 October 2020}}</ref>

On 7 September 2020, Luiz Henrique renewed his contract until September 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/fluminense/noticia/fluminense-renova-com-luiz-henrique-recem-promovido-da-base-ate-setembro-de-2025.ghtml|title=Fluminense renova com Luiz Henrique, recém-promovido da base, até setembro de 2025|trans-title=Fluminense renew with Luiz Henrique, recently promoted from the youth setup, until September 2025|publisher=GloboEsporte.com|language=pt-BR|date=7 September 2020|accessdate=5 October 2020}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 17 October, netting the opener in a 2–2 home draw against [[Ceará Sporting Club|Ceará]].

===Real Betis===
In summer 2022, Luiz Henrique moved to [[Real Betis]], agreeing to a contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |title=OFICIAL: Real Betis confirma contratação de Luiz Henrique, do Fluminense |url=https://tntsports.com.br/melhorfuteboldomundo/OFICIAL-Real-Betis-confirma-contratacao-de-Luiz-Henrique-do-Fluminense-20220701-0017.html |website=TNT Sports |access-date=15 September 2022 |language=pt |date=1 July 2022}}</ref>

=== Botafogo ===
On 31 January 2024, John Textor, owner of Eagle Football and majority shareholder of [[Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas|Botafogo]], announced the signing of Luiz Henrique, at the time the biggest signing in Brazilian football history, worth 106.6 million reals. Henrique was signed for one season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=2024-02-01 |title=Com provocação a rivais, Botafogo mostra poderio financeiro e anuncia contratação de Luiz Henrique |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/com-provocacao-a-rivais-botafogo-mostra-poderio-financeiro-e-anuncia-contratacao-de-luiz-henrique/ |access-date=2024-04-09 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref>

At the State Championship, against Volta Redonda, in the second game for Botafogo, Luiz Henrique left the field in the 78th minute with a calf injury.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=2024-02-15 |title=Luiz Henrique sente panturrilha contra o Volta Redonda e preocupa Botafogo às vésperas da Libertadores |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/luiz-henrique-sente-panturilha-contra-o-volta-redonda-e-preocupa-botafogo-as-vesperas-da-libertadores/ |access-date=2024-04-09 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref> The injury was confirmed by Botafogo on February 16, in an official statement.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=2024-02-16 |title=Botafogo lança nota para revelar grau da lesão de Luiz Henrique; leia |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/botafogo-lanca-nota-para-revelar-grau-da-lesao-de-luiz-henrique-leia/ |access-date=2024-04-09 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref>

Luiz Henrique returned to play for Botafogo on 31 March in the 2-0 victory over Boavista, in the second game of the Rio Cup final. The striker played the opening 45 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-31 |title=Luiz Henrique analisa primeiro tempo do Botafogo contra o Boavista: 'Jogando bem, mas precisamos ajustar a última bola' |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/luiz-henrique-analisa-primeiro-tempo-do-botafogo-contra-o-boavista-jogando-bem-mas-precisamos-ajustar-a-ultima-bola/ |access-date=2024-04-09 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Botafogo in a 3-1 win over [[Club Universitario de Deportes|Universitario]] in Copa Libertadores.

In the [[2024 Copa Libertadores final]], Luiz Henrique scored the opening goal of Botafogo's win. He was elected man of the match and of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-30 |title=Melhor da final, Luiz Henrique comemora título: 'Estou vivendo um sonho' |url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2024/11/30/melhor-da-final-luiz-henrique-comemora-titulo-estou-vivendo-um-sonho.htm |access-date=2024-12-01 |website=UOL |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-30 |title=Herói da final e eleito melhor da Libertadores, Luiz Henrique desabafa: 'Tentaram acabar comigo' |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/futebol/botafogo/noticia/2024/11/30/heroi-da-final-e-eleito-melhor-da-libertadores-luiz-henrique-desabafa-tentaram-acabar-comigo.ghtml |access-date=2024-12-01 |website=O Globo |language=pt-br}}</ref>

===Zenit Saint Petersburg===
On 20 January 2025, Russian champions [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit St. Petersburg]] announced the transfer of Luiz Henrique to Zenit, with [[Artur (footballer, born 1998)|Artur]] moving in the opposite direction, and [[Wendel (footballer, born 1997)|Wendel]] also moving to Botafogo at the end of the 2024–25 Russian season. Luiz Henrique signed a contract with Zenit for four years, with an optional fifth year.<ref name="LuizHenrique">{{cite web|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|url=https://fc-zenit.ru/news/2025-01-20-zenit-i-botafogo-dostigli-soglasheniya-o-perekhode-igrokov.htm|title=«Зенит» и «Ботафого» достигли соглашения о переходе игроков|trans-title=Zenit and Botafogo agreed on player transfers|date=20 January 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

==International career==
Luiz Henrique made his debut for the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] on 6 September 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against Ecuador at the [[Estádio Couto Pereira]]. He started the game and played 62 minutes in Brazil's 1-0 win.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/684610/ecuador-brazil|title=Brazil v Ecuador game report|date=6 September 2024}}</ref>

